criteria.textblock:
        Case Inclusion and Exclusion Criteria:

        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Ischemic brain injury within 12 hours of symptom onset;

          2. Including primary ischemic brain injury from embolism or arterial occlusion or
             secondary due to increased ICP after trauma, subarachnoid hemorrhage.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Patients who are hemodynamically unstable for venipunctures;

          2. Anemic patients (hemoglobin < 11);

          3. Children;

          4. Pregnant women.

        Controls Inclusion and Exclusion Criteria:

        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Healthy adults without any neurologic or systemic disease;

          2. Inpatient or outpatient adults with a chronic stroke (greater than 3 months) or
             chronic neurologic disease such as neurodegenerative disease, movement disorder,
             demyelinating disease;

          3. Inpatient or outpatient adults with systemic vascular disease.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Patients who are hemodynamically unstable for venipunctures;

          2. Anemic patients (hemoglobin < 11);

          3. Children;

          4. Pregnant women.
